- `sections`: mirror the same section structure as in `markdown`, where each
  `content` field contains the section prose (same text as the Markdown body,
  not only the heading). A section only counts as substantive if `content` is
  non-empty prose (title-only sections do not count). Include `claims` with citations when evidence supports
  specific statements; `claims[].citations[].source_id` MUST be one of the
  listed source IDs (not the ordinal number).
- `title`: concise, specific, non-generic.

